cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.AI 

This paper presents a type analysis framework for logic programs, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO) categories. The paper also discusses the widening operator, which is a common technique used in abstract interpretation-based analyses, making the software engineering (cs.SE) category relevant. Additionally, the paper presents practical results, indicating a focus on formal methods (cs.FL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
